text: Partizánske is a town in the Trenčín Region in Slovakia. About 20,000 people live there. Partizánske is about 110 km east of Bratislava, the Slovakian capital. It is at the confluence of the Nitra and Nitrica rivers, near the Tribeč mountains. == References == == Other websites == * * Official website of town Partizánske Category:Towns in Slovakia Category:Trenčín Region
